The paper deals with the problem of compressive phase retrieval, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The structured signal being recovered is likely to be an image or video, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses compression algorithms, which are often studied in machine learning (cs.LG).
